    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-26T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="654"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841E.00/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-26T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 26, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. For the Under Secretary. Your 101, August 24, 10 p.m.<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d654fn19">Not printed; it quoted contents of telegrams No. 3874 and
                        No. 4582, <ref target="#pg_764">p. 764</ref>.</note> Appreciate information.
                    From our estimate of the situation your course is what we would have suggested.
                    Have advised Winant that in view of the situation here and of our interests in
                    Northern Ireland <pb facs="0778" n="766" xml:id="pg_766"/> some measure of
                    clemency is probably expedient. The British and Canadian Representatives here
                    hold the same opinion. Hanging six for one would shock public opinion.</p>
                <p>Sending airmail despatch on this subject and memorandum of conversation with de
                        Valera.<note n="20" xml:id="d654fn20">Neither printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
